Satellite TV operator DirecTV has pulled the plug on its campaign featuring Rob Lowe after complaints by rival Comcast . 
  The cable company complained to the Better Business Bureau that the ads featured a number of false claims . 
  A National Advertising Division report found that several of the claims couldn't be substantiated . 
  The series of ads featured the actor playing a cable customer . 
  The report highlighted inaccurate claims concerning signal reliability and better picture quality . 
 